Additional Terms â€“ Revenue Limit

1. Revenue Cap
Use of this software under the MIT License is permitted only for individuals or organizations whose annual consolidated gross revenue does not exceed $50,000,000 USD. Organizations exceeding this threshold must obtain a separate commercial license.

2. Subsidiaries and Affiliates
If an organization is part of a corporate group, holding company, or otherwise controls or is controlled by, or is under common control with, other entities, the combined annual consolidated gross revenue of the group shall be used to determine eligibility under this limit.

3. Adjustment for Inflation
The revenue cap may be adjusted periodically to account for inflation or other economic factors. The effective cap at any given time shall be published by the copyright holder.

4. Compliance
By using this software, the user represents that their organization meets the revenue criteria above. Use by an organization exceeding the threshold without a separate commercial license constitutes a violation of these terms.
